INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('3276', '2', 'Place a halibut fillet on each mound of vegetables and sprinkle with the black pepper. Top with the scallions and zest. In a small bowl, combine the soy sauce, vinegar, oil, and ginger. Spoon the mixture evenly over the halibut. Top with 4 more squares of parchment or foil and fold the edges over several times to seal.'),
('3276', '3', 'Bake for 15 minutes.'),
('3276', '4', 'Transfer each packet to a plate.'),
('3276', '5', 'Serve with a knife to slit the package open, and be careful of the steam that will escape.Tip: This beautiful meal works just as well with other types of seafood. Next time, try cod, salmon, sea scallops, or peeled and deveined shrimp.'),
('3277', '1', 'In a bowl, mix vinegar, brown sugar, and mustard.'),
('3277', '2', 'Rinse halibut and pat dry.'),
('3277', '3', 'Brush lightly all over with oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('3277', '4', 'Heat a 10- to 12-inch nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat.'),
('3277', '5', 'Add fish and cook until browned on the bottom, about 4 minutes.'),
('3277', '6', 'Turn pieces over. Spoon vinegar mixture over browned sides. Lower heat and cook until fish is opaque but still moist-looking in the center (cut to test), 4 to 5 minutes longer.'),
('3277', '7', 'Transfer to plates.'),
('3278', '1', 'Using vegetable peeler, remove peel (orange part only) of clementines. Chop peel (reserve flesh for another use).'),
('3278', '2', 'Combine chopped clementine peel, chopped parsley, minced garlic, and sea salt in small bowl. Stir in extra-virgin olive oil and set gremolata aside. DO AHEAD Gremolata can be prepared 4 hours ahead. Cover and refrigerate.Preheat oven to 350F. Using vegetable peeler, remove peel of clementine in four 2-inch-long strips (orange part only).'),
('3278', '3', 'Cut four 12-inch squares parchment paper.'),
('3278', '4', 'Place halibut fillet in center of each parchment paper square. Sprinkle with salt and freshly ground black pepper.'),
('3278', '5', 'Drizzle halibut lightly with olive oil.'),
('3278', '6', 'Place 1 clementine peel strip, cut side up, on each halibut fillet. Bring 2 edges of parchment paper together along long side of fish fillet and fold parchment edges together 3 to 4 times. Tuck both remaining edges of parchment underneath fillet to create packet and place parchment packet on rimmed baking sheet. Repeat with remaining fish fillets. DO AHEAD Halibut packets can be made 4 hours ahead. Chill on rimmed baking sheet.'),
('3278', '7', 'Bake fish just until opaque in center, about 18 minutes (to check doneness, unwrap packet and insert fork in fillet).'),
('3278', '8', 'Remove rimmed baking sheet from oven. Unwrap fish.'),
('3278', '9', 'Place halibut fillets on plates, spoon gremolata over, and serve.'),
('3280', '1', 'Mix the first 6 ingredients in a small bowl. Season salsa to taste with salt and pepper.Preheat broiler. Season fish with salt, pepper, and chile powder. Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil. place fish on foil. Broil fish until just cooked through, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('3280', '2', 'Place on plates. spoon salsa over.'),
('3281', '1', 'Toss olive oil, lemon juice and zest, almonds, garlic and parsley into a mixing bowl.'),
('3281', '2', 'Place halibut on a large baking sheet lined with aluminum foil. Season lightly with salt and black pepper and drizzle with olive oil.Divide almond and herb mixture among 4 pieces of fish and smooth over each piece to create a smooth coating.'),
('3281', '3', 'Bake at 400degF until almond mixture is slightly brown and fish is cooked through and flakes easily. about 15 minutes.'),
('3282', '1', 'Portion the fish into 6 ounce pieces and season with salt and pepper.In a large pot, add your oil, coriander seeds and thyme. Warm up to 190 degrees and slowly put in your fish fillets. Make sure the fish is submerged in oil and if it''s not, add a little more to cover.Cook until you see the fish turning white and feels firm to the touch, approximately 10-12 minutes.'),
('3282', '2', 'Remove with a spatula onto a plate until ready to serve.Rinse the potatoes and place them in a large pot with the bay leaf, peppercorns, thyme, garlic, and enough cold water to cover by 2 inches.Season well with salt and bring to a boil for 2 minutes, until just knife-tender.'),
('3282', '3', 'Remove from the heat and allow the potatoes cool in the liquid.'),
('3282', '4', 'Drain the potatoes and cut in half.Cool potatoes completely and mix with mayo, sauted onions, calabrese peppers, scallions, and red wine vinegar. Season to taste with salt and pepper.Finish by plating a fillet on top of a serving of potato salad and spooning a little of the caviar on top of the fish.'),
('3286', '1', 'Pit and peel avocado and cut into 1/4-inch cubes. With a sharp knife, cut and discard peel and white pith from orange.'),
('3286', '2', 'Cut between membranes to release orange segments into a bowl.'),
('3286', '3', 'In a strainer, rinse and drain quinoa. In a 3- to 4-quart pan over high heat, bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil.'),
('3286', '4', 'Add quinoa and 1/2 teaspoon salt and adjust heat to maintain a simmer. Cover and cook until water is absorbed and quinoa is tender to bite, about 15 minutes.'),
('3286', '5', 'Meanwhile, rinse halibut and pat dry. Sprinkle lightly all over with salt and pepper.'),
('3286', '6', 'Pour oil into a 10- to 12-inch nonstick frying pan over high heat. When hot, add halibut and cook, turning once, until opaque but still moist-looking at the center of the thickest part (cut to test), about 6 minutes total.'),
('3286', '7', 'Spread about 1 teaspoon marmalade over each piece of fish.'),
('3286', '8', 'Mound quinoa on dinner plates. With a spatula, place a piece of fish on top of quinoa and arrange avocado and orange segments over fish. Sprinkle evenly with cranberries and hazelnuts.'),
('3287', '1', 'Heat a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('3287', '2', 'Add the olive oil to pan, swirling to coat.'),
('3287', '3', 'Add leeks and 1/2 teaspoon kosher salt to pan. cover and cook 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('3287', '4', 'Add 3/4 cup water to pan. bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 6 minutes or until leeks are tender.'),
('3287', '5', 'Remove from heat. Stir in raisins, vinegar, and 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper. keep warm.'),
('3287', '6', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Sprinkle fish evenly with 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt and 1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper.'),
('3287', '7', 'Add fish to pan. cook 4 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3287', '8', 'Serve fish with leek mixture.'),
('3289', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375F.'),
('3289', '2', 'Brush large rimmed baking sheet with olive oil.'),
('3289', '3', 'Heat 3 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('3289', '4', 'Add bell pepper, onion, garlic, and thyme. Saut until bell pepper is soft, about 6 minutes.'),
('3289', '5', 'Remove from heat.'),
('3289', '6', 'Mix in olives, vinegar, and tomato paste. Season relish to taste with cayenne, salt, and pepper.'),
('3289', '7', 'Place fish on prepared baking sheet and brush with olive oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spoon enough relish over each fillet to cover. Reserve remaining relish.'),
('3289', '8', 'Bake fish until just opaque in center, about 10 minutes.'),
('3289', '9', 'Transfer fish to serving platter.'),
('3289', '10', 'Garnish with thyme sprigs. serve with reserved relish.'),
('3290', '1', 'In a skillet, bring the stout and honey to a boil. Simmer over moderate heat, skimming, until reduced to 1/2 cup, 25 minutes.'),
('3290', '2', 'Pour into a heatproof bowl and stir in the lemon juice, hot sauce and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. let cool to room temperature.'),
('3290', '3', 'In a shallow baking dish, pour half of the stout glaze over the halibut fillets and turn to coat thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning a few times. Reserve the remaining stout glaze.'),
('3290', '4', 'Preheat the broiler. Bring a saucepan of water to a boil.'),
('3290', '5', 'Add the carrots and boil until just tender, about 4 minutes. drain.'),
('3290', '6', 'Pour the reserved stout glaze into the saucepan and boil over high heat until thickened and reduced to 1/3 cup, about 2 minutes.'),
('3290', '7', 'Add the carrots and simmer until glazed, about 1 minute.'),
('3290', '8', 'Remove the halibut from the marinade and arrange the fillets on a rimmed baking sheet.'),
('3290', '9', 'Brush the halibut with olive oil and season with pepper. Broil about 4 inches from the heat until richly browned and just cooked through, about 4 minutes.'),
('3290', '10', 'Transfer the halibut to plates and serve with the Guinness-glazed carrots.'),
('3291', '1', 'A day before you plan to make this, put the whole potatoes in a pot just big enough to hold all 4 and cover with water. Liberally salt the water then add about 2 tablespoons of earl grey tea. Bring to a boil and check the color of the water, it should be a dark brown color, if it isn''t add more tea. Turn the heat down to maintain a gentle simmer then cook until you can just pass a fork into the center of a potato. Turn off the heat and let the potatoes cool in the liquid, then refrigerate overnight.To start the panzanella, toss the bread cubes in 1 tablespoon of olive oil and some black pepper.'),
('3291', '2', 'Spread on a baking sheet in one layer and put into a 300 degree oven until the cubes are golden brown and crisp.'),
('3291', '3', 'Remove from the oven and allow to cool. In a medium bowl, add the chopped earl grey potato, tomato, corn, and mitsuba.For the dressing, whisk all the ingredients together. The wasabi starts loosing its potency as soon as it''s grated, so make sure you submerge it in the oil and yuzu juice quickly.For the halibut, start heating a cast iron skillet over medium heat while you prep the fish so it gets very very hot. Rub all sides of the fillets with paper towels to remove as much moisture as possible. It''s important that you get it as dry as possible to get it to crisp on the outside. When the pan is hot add a 2 tablespoons of a high smoke point oil to the pan then sprinkle just the skin side of the halibut with salt and white pepper.'),
('3291', '4', 'Put the fillets skin-side down into the pan and fry undisturbed until it is opaque half way up the fillets and they easily come off the pan. Use paper towels to carefully dry the non-skin surface of the halibut (be careful, the oil will sputter), then salt and pepper this side. Flip the halibut and continue to fry until it''s golden brown on the flesh side and cooked through (about half as much time as you cooked it on the skin side).'),
('3291', '5', 'Transfer the fillets to a plate while you finish the panzanella.To finish the panzanella, add the bread cubes and dressing to the bowl of vegetables and toss to coat everything with the dressing. Put down a layer of panzanella onto a plate then top with a halibut fillet.'),
('3292', '1', 'Heat oven to 375 F.'),
('3292', '2', 'Place the halibut fillets in a 9-inch square baking dish.'),
('3292', '3', 'Pour the wine over the fish.'),
('3292', '4', 'Drizzle with 1 tablespoon of the oil and season with 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and 1/4 teaspoon of the pepper. Scatter the olives, rosemary, and garlic over the top.'),
('3292', '5', 'Bake until the fish is the same color throughout and flakes easily, about 15 minutes. Meanwhile, heat the remaining oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('3292', '6', 'Add the potatoes and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and tender, 15 to 17 minutes.'),
('3292', '7', 'Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate. Season the potatoes with the remaining salt and pepper and serve alongside the halibut and olives.'),
('3293', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 350F. Arrange halibut in the middle of a 12x12-inch piece of parchment paper.'),
('3293', '2', 'Drizzle both sides with oil. Top with lemon and arrange tomatoes, artichoke hearts and parsley over the top and around the sides. Season all over with salt and pepper.Fold up parchment like a package, making sure the seam is at the top, to seal the ingredients inside. tuck under the ends.'),
('3293', '3', 'Transfer to a baking sheet and bake until fish is just cooked through, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('3293', '4', 'Transfer package to a plate and carefully open the parchment paper to release steam before serving.'),
('3294', '1', 'Cook the halibut'),
('3294', '2', 'Preheat an oven to 300F. Oil a shallow baking dish just large enough to hold the fish fillets in a single layer.Season the fish lightly on both sides with salt and pepper.'),
('3294', '3', 'Place the fillets, skin side down, in the prepared dish.'),
('3294', '4', 'Bake until the fish is opaque throughout, about 8 minutes. start checking after about 5 minutes to avoid overcooking.Prepare the sauce'),
('3294', '5', 'In a food processor, combine the garlic, parsley, tarragon, olive oil, anchovy paste and the 1 Tbs. vinegar. Process until smooth, stopping once or twice to scrape down the sides of the work bowl. Season with salt, pepper and more vinegar, if needed.'),
('3294', '6', 'Transfer the fish to individual plates, top with the sauce and serve immediately.'),
('3294', '7', 'Serves 4.Adapted from Williams-Sonoma Food Made Fast Series, Seafood, by Jay Harlow (Oxmoor House, 2007).'),
('3295', '1', 'In a medium saucepan, heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('3295', '2', 'Add the shallots and cook over moderate heat until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('3295', '3', 'Add the water and simmer until reduced by half, about 6 minutes.'),
('3295', '4', 'Add the cream and simmer until reduced by one-third, about 6 minutes.'),
('3295', '5', 'Let cool for about 10 minutes.'),
('3295', '6', 'Stir the parsley into the saucepan.'),
('3295', '7', 'Transfer the sauce to a blender and coarsely puree. Return the sauce to the saucepan. Stir in the lemon juice, season the sauce with salt and pepper and keep warm.'),
('3295', '8', 'In each of 2 large nonstick skillets, heat 1 tablespoon of the remaining oil until shimmering. Season the halibut with salt and pepper and cook over high heat, turning once, until browned and just cooked, about 4 minutes.'),
('3295', '9', 'Transfer the halibut to plates.'),
('3295', '10', 'Serve with the parsley sauce.'),
('3296', '1', 'Bring a large pot of water to a boil over high heat. prepare an ice-water bath.'),
('3296', '2', 'Add salt to boiling water. return to a boil.'),
('3296', '3', 'Add fennel and cook until just tender, about 3 minutes.'),
('3296', '4', 'Drain and immediately transfer to ice-water bath to cool. drain and set aside.'),
('3297', '1', 'In a small bowl, stir together olive oil, dill, salt, sugar, and pepper. Trim fillets to the same size and thickness. Line an 8- by 8-in. baking dish with plastic wrap and lay one fillet, skin side down, on bottom. Cover with dill mixture and top with second fillet, skin side up. Cover fillets with plastic wrap (do not seal edges) and a plate just big enough to fit inside the baking dish. Top plate with a 2- to 4-lb. weight (such as a 6-pack of soda). Cure fish, chilled, 2 days, turning over and draining excess liquid after 1 day.'),
('3297', '2', 'Remove fillets, scrape off dill, rinse well, and pat dry. Thinly slice halibut on a steep angle, leaving skin behind and creating wide slices.'),
('3297', '3', 'Whisk together mustards and brown sugar and set aside.'),
('3297', '4', 'Stack bread slices and cut into 4 equal squares. Top each square with a dollop of crme frache. Arrange 1 or 2 pieces halibut over the crme frache and top with several dots of mustard sauce and a sprig of dill.'),
('3298', '1', 'To Prep: Tear off 8 squares of parchment paper. Arrange 4 on a flat surface.'),
('3298', '2', 'Place the carrots and leeks in the center of each square.'),
('3298', '3', 'Place the halibut on the vegetables. Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('3298', '4', 'Drizzle with the oil and sprinkle with the oregano. Top the fish and vegetables with the remaining squares of parchment. Fold over the edges several times to seal.'),
('3299', '1', 'Combine first 3 ingredients in a shallow dish.'),
('3299', '2', 'Place eggs in a shallow dish.'),
('3299', '3', 'Place sesame seeds in a shallow dish. Dredge fish in flour mixture. dip in eggs. Press one side of fish into sesame seeds.'),
('3299', '4', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook fish, seed-side up, 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly brown. Turn, and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Spoon Poblano Cream Sauce on plates and top with fish. Sprinkle with green onions.'),
('3300', '1', 'Heat oven to 425 degrees.'),
('3302', '1', 'Brush fillets with oil, and sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('3302', '2', 'Place fillets on a grill rack coated with cooking spray.'),
('3302', '3', 'Grill, covered with grill lid, over medium-high heat (350 to 40'),
('3302', '4', '5 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3302', '5', 'Place fillets on individual serving plates. sprinkle evenly with Lemon-Mint Gremolata, and serve with lemon wedges.'),
('3303', '1', 'Rinse watercress and drain well. Pick tender sprigs from stems and cut into 3- to 4-inch lengths. you should have 1 1/2 to 2 cups sprigs. Coarsely chop remaining watercress and stems. you should have 1/3 to 1/2 cup.'),
('3303', '2', 'In a blender or food processor, whirl chopped watercress, olive oil, pine nuts, lemon peel, and garlic until finely ground.'),
('3303', '3', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.'),
('3303', '4', 'Rinse fish and pat dry.'),
('3303', '5', 'Cut into four equal pieces. Set slightly apart in an oiled 10- by 15-inch baking pan. Reserve 2 tablespoons pesto. spread remaining equally over fish.'),
('3303', '6', 'Bake in a 425 regular or convection oven until fish is barely opaque but still moist-looking in center of thickest part (cut to test), 8 to 12 minutes.'),
('3303', '7', 'Meanwhile, rinse and stem tomatoes. cut each in half. In a bowl, mix watercress sprigs, tomatoes, and reserved pesto. Spoon equally onto four dinner plates.'),
('3303', '8', 'With a wide spatula, transfer fish to plates.'),
('3303', '9', 'Add salt and pepper to taste.'),
('3303', '10', 'Garnish with lemon wedges to squeeze over fish.'),
('3304', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Season halibut with salt and pepper.'),
('3304', '2', 'In a medium saucepan, bring 2 cups salted water to a boil.'),
('3304', '3', 'Add quinoa, reduce to a simmer, cover, and cook until quinoa is tender and water has been absorbed, about 15 minutes.'),
('3304', '4', 'Remove from heat. set aside.'),
('3304', '5', 'Meanwhile, in a large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high. Cook fillets until golden, 2 to 3 minutes per side.'),
('3304', '6', 'Remove fillets from pan (reserve pan with any oil in it).'),
('3304', '7', 'Place fish in an ovenproof dish and bake 8 to 10 minutes or until just cooked through (a paring knife will easily go through fish).'),
('3304', '8', 'To pan, add ginger, bok choy, edamame, shiitakes, and snow peas. reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes or until the shiitakes begin to soften.'),
('3304', '9', 'Add green tea, soy sauce, and honey. Cook until edamame are tender, about 3 minutes longer.'),
('3304', '10', 'Add scallions to pan.'),
('3304', '11', 'Place some broth and vegetables in each of four shallow bowls. Top with fish fillet and garnish with basil leaves.'),
('3304', '12', 'Season quinoa with salt if necessary and serve on the side in separate serving bowls.'),
('3305', '1', 'Cut onion bulbs in half lengthwise (quarter if large).'),
('3305', '2', 'Cut enough onion tops into 2" lengths to measure 1 cup.'),
('3305', '3', 'Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until almost smoking.'),
('3305', '4', 'Add onion bulbs, cut side down. cook until golden, about 3 minutes.'),
('3305', '5', 'Transfer to a plate.'),
('3305', '6', 'Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in same skillet.'),
('3305', '7', 'Add squash. cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and just tender, about  5 minutes. Stir in onion bulbs, 1 cup onion tops, and 1 Tbsp. thyme leaves. season with salt and pepper and cook until onion tops wilt, about 1 minute longer.'),
('3305', '8', 'Remove from heat. set squash mixture aside.'),
('3305', '9', 'Heat remaining 2 Tbsp. oil in a large nonstick or cast-iron skillet over medium-high heat. Season halibut with salt.'),
('3305', '10', 'Add fish and thyme sprigs to skillet and cook until fish is golden brown, about 5 minutes. Turn fish and cook until just cooked through and opaque in the center, about 2 minutes longer. Divide onion-squash saut among plates. top with halibut.'),
('3306', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('3306', '2', 'Add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('3306', '3', 'Add the olives, orange segments, and tomatoes. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.'),
('3306', '4', 'Add the salt, pepper, and halibut to the pan. Spoon the sauce over the halibut. Cover and simmer until cooked through, about 7 minutes. Divide the halibut and sauce among individual plates and sprinkle with the dill.Tip: Try this bold combination of flavors and colors with other seafood, including cod, shrimp, and salmon.'),
('3307', '1', 'Sprinkle fillets evenly with salt and pepper.'),
('3307', '2', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until hot.'),
('3307', '3', 'Add fillets, in batches, and cook 3 minutes on each side or until fish flakes with a fork.'),
('3307', '4', 'Place fillets on a serving platter. Spoon Shrimp Succotash over fillets, and drizzle with Beurre Blanc.'),
('3309', '1', 'In a small skillet, toast the sesame seeds over moderate heat, stirring a few times until golden, 3 to 4 minutes. In a small bowl, mix the soy sauce with the rice vinegar, mirin, grapeseed and sesame oils, scallions and ginger. In a large, shallow dish, brush the halibut fillets with half of the soy-ginger dressing. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes.'),
('3309', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 45'),
('3309', '3', 'Transfer the halibut to a large, rimmed baking sheet and season with pepper.'),
('3309', '4', 'Bake the fish in the upper third of the oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until glazed and just cooked through.'),
('3309', '5', 'Spoon the rice into shallow bowls. Set the halibut fillets on top and spoon the spinach alongside.'),
('3309', '6', 'Pour the remaining dressing over the fish, sprinkle with the toasted sesame seeds and serve.'),
('3310', '1', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.'),
('3310', '2', 'Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, 5 to 6 minutes.'),
('3310', '3', 'Add the garlic and sweet potato and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.'),
('3310', '4', 'Add the broth and lentils and simmer, covered, until the lentils are tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Season with 1/2 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Meanwhile, heat the remaining tablespoon of oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Season the fish with 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Cook until opaque throughout, 3 to 5 minutes per side. In a bowl, whisk together the mustard, wine, and tarragon.'),
('3310', '5', 'Drizzle over the fish and lentils. Tip: Tossed with the mustard sauce, the lentils make a delicious side dish for sausage, pork, or lamb.'),
('3311', '1', 'In a small bowl, combine the vinegar and onion with 1/2 teaspoon of salt.'),
('3311', '2', 'Let stand for 10 minutes, then whisk in the honey, cilantro, mustard, garlic and 1/4 cup of the olive oil.'),
('3311', '3', 'Meanwhile, in a small skillet, heat 1 teaspoon of the olive oil over high heat until just smoking.'),
('3311', '4', 'Add the jalapeo and cook, turning, until charred and blistered on all sides, about 2 minutes. let cool slightly. Slip off the charred skin. Discard the stem and cut the jalapeo in half lengthwise. Scrape out the seeds and finely chop the jalapeo. Stir the jalapeo into the vinaigrette and season with salt and pepper.'),
('3311', '5', 'In a large nonstick skillet, heat the remaining 1/4 cup of olive oil over moderately high heat. Season the halibut fillets with salt and pepper and cook, turning once, until they are opaque throughout, about 8 minutes.'),
('3311', '6', 'Transfer the halibut to a platter.'),
('3311', '7', 'Whisk the vinaigrette, spoon it over the fish and serve with avocado wedges or watercress.'),
('3312', '1', 'Mix Marinade'),
('3312', '2', 'Mix, orange juice, oil and lemon juice in small bowl.'),
('3312', '3', 'Place halibut in large resealable plastic bag or glass dish.'),
('3312', '4', 'Add marinade. turn to coat well.Refrigerate 15 minutes or longer for extra flavor.'),
('3312', '5', 'Remove halibut from marinade. Discard any remaining marinade.Grill over medium-high heat 4 to 6 minutes per side or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3313', '1', 'Cut the oranges into segments, removing the surrounding membranes (see Shortcut, below). Squeeze the membranes over a bowl to catch their juices.'),
('3313', '2', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('3313', '3', 'Add the ginger and cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 minutes. Sprinkle the halibut with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, and the cumin. Cook for 4 minutes. Turn, add the scallions and oranges with any liquid, and continue cooking until the fish is the same color throughout and flakes easily, 4 to 5 minutes.Cook the pasta according to the package directions while the halibut cooks.Divide the pasta and fish among individual plates. Spoon the oranges and sauce over the top and sprinkle with the cilantro. Shortcut: To section an orange and remove its membranes without making a mess, cut away the peel and white pith with a knife. Then, working over a bowl, with the orange in one hand, make a cut on either side of each segment, inside its surrounding membrane. The sections will be free in no time.'),
('3314', '1', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('3314', '2', 'Cut bell peppers in half. discard seeds and membranes.'),
('3314', '3', 'Place bell peppers, skin sides up, on a baking sheet. flatten. Broil 10 minutes or until blackened.'),
('3314', '4', 'Add ancho. broil 2 minutes.'),
('3314', '5', 'Place bell peppers in a paper bag. close tightly.'),
('3314', '6', 'Let stand 5 minutes. peel.'),
('3314', '7', 'Place bell peppers, ancho, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and next 8 ingredients (through bread) in a food processor. process until smooth.'),
('3314', '8', 'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon salt over fish. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('3314', '9', 'Add fish to pan. cook 6 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness. Top with sauce. serve with lemon wedges.'),
('3315', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('3315', '2', 'Add the onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
('3315', '3', 'Add the squash, garlic, jalapeo,  teaspoon salt, and  teaspoon pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the squash begins to soften, 3 to 4 minutes.Stir in the tomatoes and their liquid. Season the halibut with  teaspoon salt and  teaspoon pepper and nestle it among the vegetables.Cover and simmer over medium-low heat until the halibut is opaque throughout and beginning to flake, 10 to 12 minutes.'),
('3316', '1', 'Preheat oven to 35'),
('3316', '2', 'To prepare sauce, combine first 6 ingredients in a food processor. process until garlic is finely chopped.'),
('3316', '3', 'Add parsley leaves, cilantro, capers, rind, and juice. pulse until herbs are coarsely chopped.'),
('3316', '4', 'To prepare fish, sprinkle fish with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('3316', '5', 'Place fish on a foil-lined baking sheet coated with cooking spray.'),
('3316', '6', 'Bake at 350 for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('3316', '7', 'Serve fish with sauce.'),
('3316', '8', 'Garnish with parsley sprigs, if desired.'),
('3317', '1', 'Cook the bacon in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until crisp.'),
('3317', '2', 'Remove bacon from pan, and crumble. Set aside.'),
('3317', '3', 'Combine 1/2 teaspoon salt, smoked paprika, and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper in a small bowl. Sprinkle spice mixture evenly over fish.'),
('3317', '4', 'Add fish to drippings in pan, and cook for 3 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3317', '5', 'Remove fish from pan, and keep warm.'),
('3317', '6', 'Add 2 teaspoons garlic to pan, and cook for 1 minute, stirring frequently. Stir in bacon.'),
('3317', '7', 'Add spinach to pan, and cook for 1 minute or until the spinach begins to wilt.'),
('3317', '8', 'Serve with fish.'),
('3318', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450F.'),
('3318', '2', 'Brush large rimmed baking sheet with 1 tablespoon oil.'),
('3318', '3', 'Mix dill and peel in small bowl for gremolata.'),
('3318', '4', 'Place beets in medium glass bowl. add enough water to cover beets halfway. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on high until just tender, 8 to 10 minutes. Uncover and drain. Cool beets slightly. Peel and cut into 1/4- to 1/3-inch-thick slices. Return beets to same bowl.'),
('3318', '5', 'Add 1 tablespoon oil, 1 tablespoon gremolata, and shallots. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. toss well. Toss beet greens in another medium bowl with 1 tablespoon oil. sprinkle with salt and pepper.'),
('3318', '6', 'Spread beet slices in single layer on half of prepared baking sheet. Mound beet greens on other half of baking sheet. Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. place fish fillets atop beet greens.'),
('3318', '7', 'Brush fish with remaining 2 tablespoons oil. Sprinkle fish with 2 tablespoons gremolata.Roast fish and vegetables until fish is just opaque in center, about 8 minutes. Divide fish and vegetables among plates. Sprinkle with remaining gremolata and serve.'),
('3319', '1', 'Prepare grill to medium-high heat.'),
('3319', '2', 'Combine first 3 ingredients. rub over halibut fillets. Cover and let stand at room temperature 10 minutes. Sprinkle fish with salt.'),
('3319', '3', 'Place fish on grill rack coated with cooking spray. grill 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('3319', '4', 'Serve with lemon wedges.'),
('3321', '1', 'Heat a 12-in. nonstick frying pan over medium-high heat with 1 tbsp. oil. Rub halibut with 1/4 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper. Lightly brown fish in frying pan on one side only, 3 to 4 minutes.'),
('3321', '2', 'Transfer to a plate.'),
('3321', '3', 'Add remaining oil to frying pan along with fennel and ouzo. Cook, stirring frequently, until light golden and almost tender, about 8 minutes.'),
('3321', '4', 'Add garlic and cook, stirring, until fragrant, 1 minute.'),
('3321', '5', 'Add tomatoes, 1/2 cup water, chickpeas, remaining salt and pepper, and the oregano and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to maintain a steady simmer. Lay halibut fillets, browned side up, in sauce and simmer until fish is cooked through, 5 to 10 minutes.'),
('3323', '1', 'To prepare the vinaigrette, combine first 6 ingredients in a small bowl. stir with a whisk.'),
('3323', '2', 'To prepare fish, heat a nonstick grill pan over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Sprinkle fish with 1/2 teaspoon salt.'),
('3323', '3', 'Add fish to pan. grill 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness. Spoon vinaigrette over fish. Sprinkle with chives.'),
('3325', '1', 'Pat fish dry with paper towels. Season fish with 1/4 tsp. salt and 1/4 tsp. pepper. Cook fish in hot oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes with a fork and is opaque throughout.'),
('3325', '2', 'Transfer fish to a serving platter, and keep warm.'),
('3325', '3', 'Add onion and garlic to skillet, and saut 1 to 2 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in capers, basil, oregano, and remaining 1/4 tsp. salt. cook 1 minute. Reduce heat to low, add tomatoes, and cook, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. Top fish with tomato sauce.'),
('3325', '4', '*Frozen halibut or fresh or frozen cod may be substituted.'),
('3326', '1', 'In a medium bowl, stir together olives, parsley, lemon zest, and olive oil.'),
('3328', '1', 'Cook rice according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.'),
('3328', '2', 'Drain and keep warm.'),
('3328', '3', 'Cook bacon in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat until crisp.'),
('3328', '4', 'Remove bacon from pan. crumble.'),
('3328', '5', 'Add onion, thyme, and mushrooms to drippings in pan. saut for 3 minutes.'),
('3328', '6', 'Remove mushroom mixture from pan.'),
('3328', '7', 'Heat oil in pan over medium heat. Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.'),
('3328', '8', 'Add fish to pan, and cook for 2 minutes on each side or until browned. Return the mushroom mixture to pan. Stir in wine, and cook for 3 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and parsley.'),
('3328', '9', 'Serve over rice.'),
('3329', '1', 'Combine the first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl. stir in 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.'),
('3329', '2', 'Heat a grill pan over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. Sprinkle remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper over fish.'),
('3329', '3', 'Add fish to pan. cook 4 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3329', '4', 'Serve with sauce.'),
('3329', '5', 'Wine note: The green herbs and tangy citrus in the chimichurri here need a bright, herbal white: sauvignon blanc. Discover the Clayhouse label out of California''s powerhouse Central Coast. Their 2008 Sauv Blanc ($1'),
('3329', '6', 'is racy with lime, green apple, crisp stone fruit, and green herbs, with enough body to stand up to the meaty fish. Sara Schneider'),
('3331', '1', 'Heat 1 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('3331', '2', 'Add fish to pan. cook 5 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3331', '3', 'Remove fish from pan. keep warm.'),
('3331', '4', 'Add remaining 1 teaspoon oil to pan.'),
('3331', '5', 'Add onion, green onions, and ginger. saut 2 minutes. Stir in coconut milk and the next 4 ingredients (through coriander). Bring to a boil. cook 1 minute.'),
('3331', '6', 'Remove from heat. Stir in basil and juice.'),
('3332', '1', 'Sprinkle fish with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.'),
('3332', '2', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('3332', '3', 'Add fish to pan. cook 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3332', '4', 'Combine fennel, orange, fennel frond, remaining 1 tablespoon oil, remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon pepper. toss gently.'),
('3332', '5', 'Serve with fish.'),
('3333', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a small bowl. rub over both sides of fillets.'),
('3333', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('3333', '3', 'Add fillets. cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until fillets flake easily when tested with a fork.'),
('3333', '4', 'Serve with lemon wedges.'),
('3334', '1', 'Combine juice and fish in a zip-top plastic bag. seal. Marinate in refrigerator 2 hours, turning once.'),
('3334', '2', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('3334', '3', 'Add onion to pan. cook 8 minutes or until tender, stirring frequently. Increase heat to medium-high. Stir in tomato, 2 tablespoons pimiento, capers, chopped jalapeo, and salt. Cover and cook 5 minutes.'),
('3334', '4', 'Add 1/4 cup water and fish. cover and cook fish 3 minutes on each side. Uncover and cook 3 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3334', '5', 'Place 1 fillet on each of 4 plates. Top each serving with 1/4 cup sauce. Sprinkle each serving with 1 1/2 teaspoons remaining pimiento.'),
('3334', '6', 'Garnish each serving with 1 lime wedge.'),
('3334', '7', 'Wine note: Halibut with Caper Sauce is perfect with a mild-tasting sauvignon blanc, which picks up on the "green" briny flavors of the capers and is delicate enough to match well with the fish. Try Dry Creek Vineyard Fum Blanc 2005 from Sonoma County, California, about $ (Fum blanc is another name for sauvignon blanc.) With its bright, refreshing, limey flavors and clean, pure taste, it''s just right for the dish. --Karen MacNeil'),
('3336', '1', 'Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat. simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes or until mixture thickens. Cool slightly.'),
('3336', '2', 'Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper.'),
('3336', '3', 'Drizzle with olive oil.'),
('3336', '4', 'Place fish on a foillined baking sheet coated with cooking spray.'),
('3336', '5', 'Bake at 425 for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Top with chutney.'),
('3338', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 37'),
('3338', '2', 'In a saucepan of boiling water, cook the carrots for 1 minute.'),
('3338', '3', 'Add the asparagus and sugar snaps and cook until crisp-tender, 2 minutes.'),
('3338', '4', 'Drain and spread on a plate to cool.'),
('3338', '5', 'In a nonstick skillet, heat the 2 tablespoons of oil until shimmering.'),
('3338', '6', 'Add the onion and mushrooms, season with salt and pepper, and cook over moderately high heat, stirring until softened, 7 minutes.'),
('3338', '7', 'Transfer to the plate. let cool slightly.'),
('3338', '8', 'Heat 2 large, sturdy baking sheets in the oven. Lay out eight 14-inch-long sheets of parchment paper and brush with olive oil. Mound some of the vegetables on half of each sheet. Set the fillets on the vegetables and season with salt and pepper. Fold each packet in half, then fold up 2 sides to seal, leaving 1 side open. In a small bowl, combine the stock and sherry. spoon 1 1/2 tablespoons into each packet. Fold up the last side, sealing tightly.'),
('3338', '9', 'Transfer the packets to the preheated baking sheets.'),
('3338', '10', 'Bake for 9 minutes, until the fish is cooked through. Open the packets and transfer the fish, vegetables and broth to plates.'),
('3338', '11', 'Serve at once.'),
('3339', '1', 'Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper.'),
('3339', '2', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('3339', '3', 'Add fish. cook 3 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3339', '4', 'Place 1 cup salad greens (prepared as described above) on each plate.'),
('3339', '5', 'Serve with Gazpacho Salsa topped with fish.'),
('3342', '1', 'Preheat oven to 45'),
('3342', '2', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a shallow dish.'),
('3342', '3', 'Place egg whites and egg in a shallow dish.'),
('3342', '4', 'Place flour in a shallow dish. Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Dredge fish in flour. Dip in egg mixture. dredge in panko mixture.'),
('3342', '5', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('3342', '6', 'Add 3 fish fillets. cook 2 1/2 minutes on each side or until browned.'),
('3342', '7', 'Place fish on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Repeat procedure with remaining 1 tablespoon oil and remaining fish.'),
('3342', '8', 'Bake at 450 for 6 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3345', '1', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle fish evenly with salt and pepper.'),
('3345', '2', 'Add fish to pan. cook 5 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3345', '3', 'Remove fish from pan. keep warm.'),
('3345', '4', 'Add garlic to pan. cook 30 seconds, stirring constantly. Stir in tomato, broth, wine, and beans. bring to a boil. Reduce heat, and simmer 5 minutes.'),
('3345', '5', 'Remove from heat. stir in rosemary.'),
('3345', '6', 'Serve immediately.'),
('3346', '1', 'In a small bowl combine mango, green onions, parsley and lime juice. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.'),
('3346', '2', 'In a small saucepan over medium heat combine maple syrup and mustard. bring to boiling. Reduce heat to low. simmer 5 minutes.'),
('3346', '3', 'Remove from heat and let cool.'),
('3346', '4', 'Coat grill rack with nonstick cooking spray. Preheat grill to medium (300F to 350F). Season filets with salt to taste.'),
('3346', '5', 'Brush with syrup mixture.'),
('3346', '6', 'Place fillets on grill. Grill, covered, 5 minutes per side or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3346', '7', 'Just before serving, stir goat cheese into mango mixture. Spoon over fillets, and serve.'),
('3347', '1', 'Whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, water, garlic, shallot, red-pepper flakes, and 1/2 tsp each of salt and pepper until salt has dissolved. Stir in parsley.'),
('3347', '2', 'Let chimichurri stand 20 minutes.'),
('3347', '3', 'Meanwhile, prepare grill for direct-heat cooking over medium-hot charcoal (medium heat for gas).'),
('3347', '4', 'Pat fish dry, then brush with vegetable oil and sprinkle with 1/2 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper (total).'),
('3347', '5', 'Oil grill rack, then grill fish, covered only if using a gas grill, turning once, until just cooked through, 8 to 10 minutes total.'),
('3347', '6', 'Serve fish drizzled with some of chimichurri. serve remainder on the side.'),
