('3354', '4', 'Transfer fish to plates. Spoon sauce over and serve.'),
('3356', '1', 'Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Dredge in flour.'),
('3356', '2', 'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('3356', '3', 'Add fish and saute until lightly browned and just opaque in center, about 4 minutes per side.'),
('3356', '4', 'Transfer fish to platter.'),
('3356', '5', 'Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in same skillet.'),
('3356', '6', 'Add shallots and crushed red pepper. saute 1 minute.'),
('3356', '7', 'Mix in tomatoes, olives, 1/4 cup basil, and capers.'),
('3356', '8', 'Add clam juice and wine. Boil until sauce thickens slightly, about 4 minutes.'),
('3356', '9', 'Mix in 1/4 cup basil. Season sauce with salt and pepper. Spoon sauce over fish.'),
('3357', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F. In a small bowl, toss together onions, bell peppers, piquillo peppers and capers and set aside. Arrange fillets, skin-side down, in a large baking dish or roasting pan.'),
('3357', '2', 'Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Top with pepper mixture and bake until cooked through, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('3357', '3', 'Transfer halibut to plates and spoon peppers and pan juices over fish.'),
('3357', '4', 'Drizzle with vinegar and serve.'),
('3358', '1', 'Shred potato on the coarse side of a grater. squeeze out excess liquid.'),
('3358', '2', 'Combine shredded potato, chives, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a small bowl.'),
('3358', '3', 'Sprinkle both sides of fish fillets evenly with remaining 1/2 teaspoon each of salt and pepper. Sprinkle 1 side of each fillet with lemon rind. Pat 1/4 cup potato mixture evenly over lemon rind on each fillet.'),
('3358', '4', 'Heat 1 teaspoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. add 2 fillets, potato side down. Cook 5 to 6 minutes or until potato begins to brown.'),
('3358', '5', 'Transfer fish, potato side up, to a greased jellyroll pan. Repeat with remaining 1 teaspoon oil and remaining 2 fish fillets.'),
('3358', '6', 'Bake at 400 for 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork.'),
('3358', '7', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('3359', '1', 'To prepare aioli, combine cilantro, mayonnaise, serrano, and minced garlic, stirring well.'),
