('3375', '4', 'Transfer to a small bowl to cool.'),
('3375', '5', 'Mix in thyme.Sprinkle the fish with salt and coat evenly with the sesame seed mixture, covering the sides as well as the top.'),
('3375', '6', 'Transfer the fish to the prepared baking sheet and roast until just opaque in the center, 10 to 14 minutes.'),
('3375', '7', 'Serve with lemon wedges.'),
('3376', '1', 'Combine first 5 ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a large zip-top plastic bag. add fish. Seal and marinate in refrigerator 1 hour, turning occasionally.'),
('3376', '2', 'Preheat broiler.'),
('3376', '3', 'Spoon yogurt onto several layers of heavy-duty paper towels. spread to 1/2-inch thickness. Cover with additional paper towels. let stand 5 minutes.'),
('3376', '4', 'Scrape into a bowl using a rubber spatula.'),
('3376', '5', 'Add 1/4 teaspoon salt, shredded fennel bulb, chopped fennel fronds, and garlic. Cover and refrigerate.'),
('3376', '6', 'Remove fish from bag. discard marinade.'),
('3376', '7', 'Place fish on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray. Broil 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.'),
('3376', '8', 'Serve with yogurt sauce.'),
('3377', '1', 'Combine first 8 ingredients.'),
('3377', '2', 'Combine water and next 5 ingredients (through cilantro sprig) in a large skillet. bring to a low simmer (180 to 190).'),
('3377', '3', 'Add fish. cook 10 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3377', '4', 'Remove fish from pan with a slotted spoon. drain on paper towels.'),
('3377', '5', 'Serve with sauce.'),
('3377', '6', 'Sustainable Choice: Halibut is a readily available, sustainable option with mild flavor and firm flesh.'),
('3379', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl, tossing gently.'),
('3379', '2', 'Brush halibut with oil. place, skin side up, on grill. Grill, covered, over medium-high heat (350 to 40'),
('3379', '3', '5 minutes. Turn fillets, and grill 5 more minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.'),
('3379', '4', 'Serve with Rhubarb Compote and balsamic strawberries.'),
('3380', '1', 'Prepare grill.'),
('3380', '2', 'Place fillets on grill rack coated with cooking spray. Sprinkle fish evenly with 1/8 teaspoon salt and pepper. Cover and grill 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3380', '3', 'While fish grills, combine 1/8 teaspoon salt, basil, and remaining 5 ingredients in a blender or food processor. Process until finely minced.'),
('3380', '4', 'Serve grilled fish over pesto.'),
('3381', '1', 'Preheat grill to medium high heat (350 to 400). Arrange 4 (12-inch-long) sheets heavy-duty aluminum foil on work surface. Divide first 3 ingredients evenly among sheets of foil. Top with halibut fillets. sprinkle fillets evenly with salt and pepper. Divide garlic evenly among fillets. top each with a rosemary sprig, and drizzle with oil. Gather sides of foil over fish and vegetables to cover completely. crimp edges to seal packets.'),
('3381', '2', 'Place fish packets on grill. Cook, turning once, 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are sizzling inside packets and fish is opaque throughout.'),
('3381', '3', 'Serve with couscous.'),
('3383', '1', 'Rinse fillets. pat dry, and sprinkle with salt.'),
('3383', '2', 'Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a shallow bowl. Dredge fillets in flour mixture, shaking off excess flour.'),
('3383', '3', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('3383', '4', 'Add fillets. cook 3 minutes on each side or until fillets are golden brown.'),
('3383', '5', 'Serve with Cornichon Sauce.'),
('3384', '1', 'Combine 1 tablespoon oil, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, parsley, and next 6 ingredients (through anchovy paste) in a small bowl, tossing well. set aside.'),
('3384', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('3384', '3', 'Add remaining 1 teaspoon oil to pan. swirl to coat. Sprinkle fish fillets evenly with salt and remaining 1/8 teaspoon black pepper.'),
('3384', '4', 'Add fish fillets to pan. cook 4 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('3384', '5', 'Serve fish with salsa verde.'),
('3385', '1', 'Drizzle the soy sauce over both sides of the halibut fillets. Cover and refrigerate.    In a 12-inch saut pan, combine the chicken broth, honey, tomato paste, vinegar, ginger, and Tabasco. Bring to a simmer over medium heat and cook gently for 12 minutes, stirring occasionally and skimming foam as necessary.'),
('3385', '2', 'Add the fillets, cover, and poach gently at a bare simmer over medium-low heat until the flllets are slightly firm to the touch and the centers are almost opaque (make a small slit with a knife to check), 6 to 8 minutes. the fish should be slightly undercooked at this point. Turn off the heat and let sit covered for another 2 minutes.    Divide the halibut and broth evenly among four shallow bowls. Sprinkle generously with the scallions and cilantro and serve with a spoon for the broth.    Serving Suggestions    Set a mound of white or brown rice into the broth with the fish.'),
('3386', '1', 'Mix the miso, orange juice, mirin, soy sauce, brown sugar and zest in a bowl.'),
('3386', '2', 'Place the halibut on a baking pan with the skin side down.'),
('3386', '3', 'Brush the top of the halibut with the orange and miso glaze.Broil in a preheated oven until the miso blaze starts to bubble, about 3 minutes.Cover the halibut with foil and continue to broil until the halibut is cooked, about 4 minutes.');